        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix Copilot unlimited chat quota display",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Decode Copilot `quota_snapshots.*.unlimited`.\n- Keep unlimited chat quota snapshots from being treated as zero-entitlement placeholders.\n- Surface unlimited Copilot chat as a secondary rate window with `0%` used instead of dropping it.\n\n## Evidence\nThe latest installed CodexBar `0.32.4` showed only the Premium lane for Copilot. The GitHub Copilot user API returned both `premium_interactions` and `chat`; the `chat` snapshot had `quota_id=chat`, `unlimited=true`, `entitlement=0`, `remaining=0`, and `percent_remaining=100`. Current placeholder handling drops that shape before it can render as Chat.\n\n## Tests\n- `swift test --filter CopilotUsageModelsTests`\n- `swift test --filter CopilotUsageFetcherTests`\n",
